// Connect to the emulator
connectStorageEmulator(storage, 'localhost', 9199);
```

These examples cover some of the basic operations you can perform with Firebase Storage, such as initializing the storage service, uploading and downloading files, deleting files, listing files in a directory, uploading strings, and connecting to the storage emulator.

