Certainly! Here are some usage examples based on the provided TypeScript definitions for the Firebase Vertex AI SDK:

### Example 1: Initializing Vertex AI and Generative Model

```typescript
import { getVertexAI, getGenerativeModel, VertexAI, GenerativeModel, GenerateContentRequest, Content, TextPart } from 'firebase';

// Initialize Firebase app (assuming you have already configured Firebase)
import { initializeApp } from 'firebase/app';
const firebaseConfig = {
    apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
    authDomain: "YOUR_AUTH_DOMAIN",
    projectId: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
    storageBucket: "YOUR_STORAGE_BUCKET",
    messagingSenderId: "YOUR_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID",
    appId: "YOUR_APP_ID"
};
const app = initializeApp(firebaseConfig);

// Initialize Vertex AI
const vertexAI: VertexAI = getVertexAI(app, { location: 'us-central1' });

// Define model parameters
const modelParams = {
    model: 'text-davinci-003',
    generationConfig: {
        maxOutputTokens: 100,
        temperature: 0.7
    }
};

// Get Generative Model
const generativeModel: GenerativeModel = getGenerativeModel(vertexAI, modelParams);

// Define content request
const contentRequest: GenerateContentRequest = {
    contents: [
        {
            role: 'user',
            parts: [{ text: 'Tell me a joke. ' } as TextPart]
        } as Content
    ]
};

// Generate content
generativeModel.generateContent(contentRequest).then(result => {
    console.log(result.response.text());
}).catch(error => {
    console.error('Error generating content:', error);
});
```

### Example 2: Using ChatSession for Multi-turn Chats

```typescript
import { getVertexAI, VertexAI, ChatSession, StartChatParams, Content, TextPart } from 'firebase';

// Initialize Firebase app (assuming you have already configured Firebase)
import { initializeApp } from 'firebase/app';
const firebaseConfig = {
    apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
    authDomain: "YOUR_AUTH_DOMAIN",
    projectId: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
    storageBucket: "YOUR_STORAGE_BUCKET",
    messagingSenderId: "YOUR_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID",
    appId: "YOUR_APP_ID"
};
const app = initializeApp(firebaseConfig);

// Initialize Vertex AI
const vertexAI: VertexAI = getVertexAI(app, { location: 'us-central1' });

// Define chat session parameters
const startChatParams: StartChatParams = {
    history: [
        {
            role: 'user',
            parts: [{ text: 'Hello, how are you? ' } as TextPart]
        } as Content
    ]
};

// Start a chat session
const chatSession: ChatSession = vertexAI.startChat(startChatParams);

// Send a message in the chat session
chatSession.sendMessage('What is the weather like today?').then(result => {
    console.log(result.response.text());
}).catch(error => {
    console.error('Error sending message:', error);
});
```

### Example 3: Counting Tokens in a Request

```typescript
import { getVertexAI, VertexAI, GenerativeModel, CountTokensRequest, Content, TextPart } from 'firebase';

// Initialize Firebase app (assuming you have already configured Firebase)
import { initializeApp } from 'firebase/app';
const firebaseConfig = {
    apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
    authDomain: "YOUR_AUTH_DOMAIN",
    projectId: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
    storageBucket: "YOUR_STORAGE_BUCKET",
    messagingSenderId: "YOUR_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID",
    appId: "YOUR_APP_ID"
};
const app = initializeApp(firebaseConfig);

// Initialize Vertex AI
const vertexAI: VertexAI = getVertexAI(app, { location: 'us-central1' });

// Define model parameters
const modelParams = {
    model: 'text-davinci-003'
};

// Get Generative Model
const generativeModel: GenerativeModel = getGenerativeModel(vertexAI, modelParams);

// Define content for token counting
const content: Content[] = [
    {
        role: 'user',
        parts: [{ text: 'How many tokens are in this sentence? ' } as TextPart]
    }
];

// Create token count request
const countTokensRequest: CountTokensRequest = { contents: content };

// Count tokens
generativeModel.countTokens(countTokensRequest).then(response => {
    console.log('Total tokens:', response.totalTokens);
}).catch(error => {
    console.error('Error counting tokens:', error);
});
```

These examples demonstrate how to initialize the Vertex AI SDK, create a generative model, use a chat session, and count tokens in a request. Adjust the configurations and parameters as needed for your specific use case.

